New Spiedska: There is a great degree of uncertainty in the scientific community regarding the origins and early history of the Inkling race. While it is generally accepted that they originated from Earth, some believe that their features are too unique for that to be the case. The time of their arrival on the American continent is also a subject of debate, with estimates ranging from 16,000 to 9,000 years ago. By the time they made contact with humans, they were significantly more advanced, and the early Native Americans regarded them as superior beings - either as powerful benefactors who would periodically grant them gifts, or as feared demons capable of razing entire villages to the ground, depending on the attitudes of the various Inkling tribes they interacted with.

New Makasta: They are officially known as a "Peoples Untied Democratic Republic", which leads me to wonder what exactly that means. Is it a metaphor for freedom, or do they despise formal wear?

Dunkin' Donuts: In their world, large-scale environmental revitalisation programs have prompted the moving of heavy industry into space, and extraterrestrial development in general is far more advanced than it is in OTL. There exists a fully-fledged city in space, named Astropolis, with Dunkin' Donuts being the first Earth-based company to establish its services there.
